COVID-19 Vaccinations Progress¶

Purpose
To view vaccine doses overview by country and by vaccine types. Throughout this project, I will look into how many countries are participating vaccinations daily and by each country's population.

Emergency Use Authorization (EAU) Dates:

  • Pfizer BioNTech: December 11, 2020
  • Moderna: December 18, 2020

  • Janssen: February 27, 2021

    For more information, FDA

Data can be found here: Kaggle

Key Performance Indicators:

  • Number of countries participating vaccination
  • Daily counts per country
  • 10 most vaccinated countries per population
  • Types of vaccines have been used
  • Day of week the most people get vaccinated in United States

Conclusion

Analyzed same KPIs twice on February 23 and March 9. 28 unique countries are added in two weeks. Following combination of vaccines are most used throughout the world: Moderna, Oxford/AstraZeneca, Pfizer/BioNTech. Since US and UK are one of the most leading vaccination countries and they are using Moderna/Pfizer and Oxford/AstraZeneca, respectively, the fact that vaccine type usage is a logical conclusion. Also, Israel still stands its first place on Vaccination_per_hundred and as of 03/09/21, Israel reached 5 millionth vaccinations.
